name: White Winged Junco
description:
Common Name: White-Winged Junco
Latin Name: Junco hyemalis aikeni

A Dark-Eyed Junco subspecies that can look very similar to the common Slate-Colored Junco, the differences include being larger in size, lighter grey, and with ragged white patches on the wings often present. 

The White-Winged Junco also have a relatively small breeding range, considered endemic to the Black Hills of South Dakota, but can also be found in parts of Nebraska, Colorado, Wyoming and Montana.
